---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import LegalContent from '../components/sections/LegalContent.astro';
import ContactSection from '../components/sections/ContactSection.astro';
---

<Base
  title="AllSafe IT Privacy Policy | Protecting Our Customers"
  description="Understand how we prioritize and protect your privacy at AllSafe IT. Explore our comprehensive Privacy Policy for a secure online experience. Read more."
  canonical="https://www.allsafeit.com/privacy-policy"
>
  <LegalContent title="Privacy Policy" lastUpdated="V1.1 — Last edited 10 January 2022">

    {/* Webflow opens the policy with a lead paragraph (not a numbered
        section) — included verbatim to match the live page. */}
    <p class="lead-text"><strong>AllSafe IT</strong> (the "Company") respects the privacy of its online visitors and customers of its products and services (including, but not limited to <strong>allsafeit.com</strong>) and complies with applicable laws for the protection of your privacy.</p>

    <h2>1. Definitions</h2>
    <p>"Personal Data" means any information that relates to an identified or identifiable natural person. This includes but is not limited to: name, email address, phone number, IP address, location data, and any other information that could be used to identify you directly or indirectly.</p>

    <h2>2. Why the Company Collects and Processes Data</h2>
    <p>AllSafe IT collects and processes personal data for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>To provide and maintain our managed IT services</li>
      <li>To communicate with you about your account and services</li>
      <li>To send service-related notifications and updates</li>
      <li>To respond to inquiries and support requests</li>
      <li>To improve our services and website</li>
      <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
      <li>To detect, prevent, and address technical issues and security incidents</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. What Data We Collect and Process</h2>

    <h3>3.1 Basic Account Data</h3>
    <p>When you create an account or engage our services, we collect your name, email address, company name, phone number, and billing information.</p>

    <h3>3.2 Transaction and Payment Data</h3>
    <p>Payment information is processed through PCI-DSS compliant payment processors. AllSafe IT does not store full credit card numbers on our systems.</p>

    <h3>3.3 Other Data You Explicitly Submit</h3>
    <p>Information you provide through contact forms, support tickets, surveys, and other direct communications.</p>

    <h3>3.4 Your Use of Websites</h3>
    <p>We collect data about how you interact with our website, including pages visited, time spent, and referring URLs through analytics tools.</p>

    <h3>3.5 Your Use of Services and Other Subscriptions</h3>
    <p>Data about how you use our managed IT services, including support ticket history, system monitoring logs, and service usage metrics.</p>

    <h3>3.6 Tracking Data and Cookies</h3>
    <p>We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to improve your experience. You may control cookie settings through your browser preferences. Some features may not function correctly if cookies are disabled.</p>

    <h3>3.7 Third Party Services</h3>
    <p>We may receive information from third-party tools we use to deliver our services, such as cloud infrastructure providers, security monitoring platforms, and communication tools.</p>

    <h3>3.8 Content Recommendations</h3>
    <p>We may use data about your interests and interactions to provide relevant content recommendations on our website and in communications.</p>

    <h3>3.9 Information Required to Detect Violations</h3>
    <p>To protect the security of our systems and clients, we may collect and analyze log data and usage patterns to detect potential security incidents, fraud, or violations of our terms of service.</p>

    <h2>4. How We Store Data</h2>
    <p>Personal data is stored on secure servers located in the United States. We retain personal data for as long as necessary to provide our services and comply with legal obligations. Upon termination of a service agreement, data is retained for a period specified in the service agreement and then securely deleted.</p>

    <h2>5. Who Has Access to Data</h2>
    <p>Access to personal data is restricted to AllSafe IT employees and contractors who require it to perform their job functions. We do not sell personal data to third parties. We may share data with trusted service providers who assist us in delivering our services, subject to confidentiality agreements.</p>

    <h2>6. Your Rights and Control Mechanisms</h2>
    <p>Depending on your location, you may have rights including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>The right to access your personal data</li>
      <li>The right to correct inaccurate data</li>
      <li>The right to request deletion of your data</li>
      <li>The right to object to processing</li>
      <li>The right to data portability</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:info@allsafeit.com">info@allsafeit.com</a>.</p>

    <h2>7. Children</h2>
    <p>Our services are not directed to individuals under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If you believe we have inadvertently collected data from a minor, contact us immediately.</p>

    <h2>8. Contact Info</h2>
    <p>For questions about this privacy policy or our data practices, contact our Data Protection Officer at <a href="mailto:info@allsafeit.com">info@allsafeit.com</a> or call <a href="tel:+18884002748">888-400-2748</a>.</p>

    <h2>9. Revision Date</h2>
    <p>This policy was last updated on January 10, 2022. We reserve the right to update this policy at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date.</p>

  </LegalContent>

  <ContactSection heading="Ready to transform your IT? Contact us today!" />
</Base>
